Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}, quarter larger ones so all are equal-sized. Halve, peel, and slice @Red Onion{1} into ½-inch wedges. Place @Whole Grain Mustard{1%ounce} in a #large bowl{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}. Stir to combine.

Add potatoes and onions to mustard, and stir to coat. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Spread on a #baking sheet{}, and roast until golden brown, about ~{25-30%minutes}.

Place @Chicken Thighs{12%ounce} on another baking sheet, and season on both sides with salt, pepper, and @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon}. Roast until firm and juices run clear when pierced with a knife, about ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mince @Garlic{2%clove}(minced). Cut @Lemon{1} into wedges.

Cook the spinach: With about 5 minutes left on potatoes, heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Add @Spinach{5%ounce} and season generously with salt and pepper. Toss until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Finish and plate: Plate chicken with potatoes and onions on the side. Serve with spinach and a lemon wedge for squeezing over. Enjoy!